document.title: 2023 Indiana Academic Standards: Kindergarten - Grade 5 Physical Education

50700B5924F145C48DF3BCB03CA49EAC.description:
Describes and compares the positive social interactions when engaged in
partner, small-group and large-group physical activities.

79E26FB7ECE74D579F68E03C9F9BAD57.description: Ranks the enjoyment of participating in different physical activities.

14C7A2602C5F497DB2B48A9E7317BD56.description:
Rates the enjoyment of participating in challenging and mastered physical
activities.

AAC9EBD70A424825A9F9CDDA64EA6225.description: Examines the health benefits of participating in physical activity.

1DE1AD5779F34CF7B2511BCDFCF14C2A.description: Valuing Health, Enjoyment, Challenge, Self Expression, and Social Interaction

94C66411E6A1408F859B59809317F601.description:
The physically literate individual recognizes the value of physical activity for health,
enjoyment, challenge, self expression and/or social interaction.

D3A0BAD97A914DDFBD1C1967307C8733.description:
Works safely with peers, independently, and with/without equipment in
physical activity settings.

DDC917F23695456F9B10AEF1EFB55A81.description: Exhibits etiquette and adherence to rules in a variety of physical activities.

9E6E59BBE01248D186F275A8DB059CBD.description: Accepts players of all skill levels into the physical activity.

3BA3B15E490D428FA445FDC105463598.description: Praises the movement effort of others both more and less skilled.

42B7EA12EF9D4ECCB6D97F9462142CBE.description: Listens respectfully to corrective feedback from others (such as peers, adults).

B97608A8BD4944E297595CA42494989A.description: Reflects on personal social behavior in physical activity.

3AE0DD152648430FA0B438F7B4F09B0F.description: Exhibits responsible behavior in both independent and group situations.

E0D60CE8CDE34F47ADC29E022275A18A.description:
The physically literate individual exhibits responsible personal and social behavior
that respects self and others.

6E844EC9FB32402186D656B0D6B4601A.description:
Discusses the importance of hydration and hydration choices relative to
physical activities.

F26B253963F24EFAA60386223A2A8781.description:
Identifies areas of needed remediation from personal tests and, with teacher
assistance, identifies strategies for progress in those areas.

BDC9D446080E4432A22B24CE74C6BD83.description:
Demonstrates warmup and cool- down relative to the cardiorespiratory fitness
assessment.

5411B73829C542F3840BFF37744B72CE.description: Identifies the five components of health-related fitness.

14C388E0149E44B7B3E096938917276A.description:
Actively engages in the activities of physical education class, both teacher
directed and independent.

CBA96F376D3C4660B99A3316E00D7419.description:
Analyzes opportunities for participating in physical activity outside physical
education class.

AFC2A0F1632A44509900EC01952989AD.description:
The physically literate individual demonstrates the knowledge and skills to achieve
and maintain a health-enhancing level of physical activity and fitness.

5C4D93CBC33A4D75AC038106C83540E3.description: Recognizes the types of kicks needed for different games and sports situations.

31AD277D02E34C168343E0E3CF0286F0.description: Applies simple defensive strategies/ tactics in chasing and fleeing activities.

B5FD22EC80FD4862BE61DCBF8A0DD1D8.description: Applies simple offensive strategies and tactics in chasing and fleeing activities.

BB42B7EF7F5843F5BA5D86CF7B61BCD1.description:
Applies the concepts of direction and force when striking an object sending it
toward a designated target.

DFF6250B2BCE437297C0BBF11AC6A8E2.description: Applies the movement concepts of speed, endurance and pacing for running.

C3BA5DEB1FBE4939B619A309960C36B9.description:
Combines movement concepts with skills in small-sided practice tasks (such as
gymnastics and dance environments).

8D381583B2B64031857A2B3D550F3837.description:
Applies the concept of open spaces to combination skills involving traveling
(such as dribbling and traveling).

E0509DD7F700408C86A8C935905B8F5E.description:
Applies the concept of open spaces to combination skills involving traveling
(such as dribbling and traveling).

E1D79F8B72EF4239BD71D084473AF255.description:
The physically literate individual applies knowledge of concepts, principles,
strategies and tactics related to movement and performance.

BDFD3BE3AA5B4EAF832EDA903C693E52.description:
Creates a jump-rope routine (such as jumping in a figure 8, front to back, etc., and
with short rope, long rope, double dutch, Jump Bands).

C27E3A2C8ACA4575BA615EB14CCD93E5.description:
Strikes an object with a long-handled implement (such as a hockey stick, golf club,
bat, tennis racket, badminton racket), while demonstrating three of the five critical elements
of a mature pattern for the implement.

81076F53D6EC40EFB934D7F4F43BEFB5.description:
Strikes an object with a short-handled implement while demonstrating a mature
pattern.

A6601006B5F5435FB70C7885A3945CF0.description:
Demonstrates mature pattern while striking an object underhand in a variety of
lead-up activities and small-sided game play.

152CFFC12D8D4A0D977E9005F8906E44.description:
Performs mature pattern while receiving with the foot when moving in a
non-dynamic environment.

A94D3C522A614B3BB229EC5DB6A10CC8.description:
Dribbles with the feet in general space with control of ball and body while
increasing and decreasing speed.

67436E581ACE4D49B2971315317909A8.description: Kicks along the ground, in the air, and punts using mature patterns.

5A2CC0F9312D4B2D8582177A44D630BA.description:
Passes and receives a ball with the outside and inside of the foot to a stationary
partner, “giving” on reception before returning the pass.

44BEA32C84554F13BF2269CD207E8B83.description:
Passes & receives a ball with the inside of the foot to a moving partner in a
non-dynamic environment

B92798A5158B4ACCA2A7752D0244CAA1.description:
Dribbles in general space with control of ball and body while increasing and
decreasing speed.

F38D70B1B9DF4789BF69BD531B0A1947.description:
Dribbles in personal space with both the preferred and the non-preferred hands
using a mature pattern.

B832CE79F4974720B55CCC38F7E9FF73.description:
Catches a thrown ball above the head, at chest or waist level, and below the waist
using a mature pattern in a non-dynamic environment

92844FEDAF8743BD9548B399C6BED8A6.description:
Passes to a moving partner with reasonable accuracy in a non-dynamic
environment.

5FD499F303ED4F1EB5778019B88806C5.description: Throws overhand to a partner or at a target with accuracy at a reasonable distance.

94E1016CC33C4E8BBD1CFC8F99E8C548.description: Throws overhand using a mature pattern in non-dynamic environments.

54B63F4316714EDC8E8450E65528536B.description: Demonstrates mature pattern in an underhand throw with accuracy.

443BF3CD75FA4BF5B3757800ACC4BEFE.description: Performs mature pattern in an underhand throw to a moving partner.

29E16639C6AF44A28CFA31969A8578D2.description:
Transfers weight from feet to hands, varying speed and using large extensions
(such as kick, handstand, cartwheel).

2000498C43034C3DA9D66E7DE35294B7.description:
Balances on different bases of support on apparatus, demonstrating levels and
shapes.

5231F72BB21D4241BC19EA381ABB122A.description:
Applies mature patterns in nonlocomotor skills in a variety of lead-up activities and
small sided game play.

A2A9EFA292B441C187AB828E8C2D9C44.description:
Combines locomotor movement patterns and dance steps to create and perform an
original dance.

FC9E03C084FC4278B00AE388156CA10A.description:
Jumps and lands in the horizontal and vertical planes using a mature pattern within
activities (such as in dance, educational gymnastics and small-sided practice tasks and
game environments).

BF27FC01DDD34993B94507550D5E0F22.description: Locomotor (Jumping and landing in a horizontal and vertical plane)

795959D5D3C34297B5629883C72AC677.description: Performs appropriate pacing in a variety of running distances.

9A4122919CD240C29EB5BA2013BC0F99.description:
Applies mature patterns in locomotor skills in a variety of lead-up activities and
small sided game play.

55E89DFA30C84C949157A636746E62C5.description: Locomotor (Hopping, galloping, running, sliding, skipping, leaping, walking, running)

374C033E04244D43ACFF6B0A666366E3.description:
The physically literate individual will demonstrate competency in a variety of motor
skills and movement patterns.
